# Movie Finder RAG — Cursor Rules

This file is a legacy fallback. Cursor loads the richer MDC rules from `.cursor/rules/` automatically.

If your IDE supports MDC rules, the following files apply:
- `.cursor/rules/project.mdc` — always active (rag context, key files)
- `.cursor/rules/python.mdc` — activates on `**/*.py` (Python standards, mypy, ruff)
- `.cursor/rules/architect.mdc` — activates when designing embedding or Qdrant changes
- `.cursor/rules/developer.mdc` — activates when implementing issues
- `.cursor/rules/debugger.mdc` — activates when investigating ingestion failures

---

## Quick reference

**Repo:** `aharbii/movie-finder-rag` · Primary context: `CLAUDE.md`

**Non-negotiables:**
- Embedding model is OpenAI `text-embedding-3-large` (3072-dim) — changing it requires full re-ingestion and an ADR
- Qdrant is always external (cloud) — no local Qdrant container, ever
- Strategy pattern for embedding providers — no `if provider == "openai":` branching
- `mypy --strict` must pass; no bare `except:`; no `print()` — use logging
- Never `--no-verify` on pre-commit
- Conventional Commits: `feat(rag): summary`
- Disclose AI tool + model in every PR
